    <h2>Masters of Food & Wine</h2>
    <p>Furthering Jay Pritzker’s original vision for the brand, Park Hyatt launched its Masters of Food & Wine program in 2003. The series showcases Park Hyatt chefs, sommeliers, and specialists through intimate, immersive culinary and beverage events all over the world.</p>
    <p>Past Masters of Food & Wine events include a twilight fishing excursion and traditional cooking class at <a href="https://www.hyatt.com/en-US/hotel/maldives/park-hyatt-maldives-hadahaa/mldph?src=corp_lclb_gmb_seo_swa_mldph" class="content-link" target="_blank">Park Hyatt Maldives Hadahaa</a> and a visit to local Argentine olive groves with an olive oil tasting at <a href="https://www.hyatt.com/en-US/hotel/argentina/park-hyatt-mendoza-hotel-casino-and-spa/menph?src=corp_lclb_gmb_seo_latam_menph" class="content-link" target="_blank">Park Hyatt Mendoza</a>. No two Masters of Food & Wine events are alike. Coming soon to <a href="https://www.hyatt.com/en-US/hotel/switzerland/park-hyatt-zurich/zurph?src=corp_lclb_gmb_seo_eame_zurph" class="content-link" target="_blank">Park Hyatt Zurich</a>, Executive Chef Frank Widmer will guide guests through a cozy Swiss chalet dinner, grilling a carefully selected menu of seasonal favorites, paired with LVMH wines.</p>
